                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5606: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bluefields</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bluefields</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-02T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>La Luz and Bonanza Mines again invaded by Sandinistas; La Luz totally destroyed,
                    Bonanza partially. Rumors indicate Marshall still in hands of invaders but
                    unharmed up to the 23rd of April. Apparently all other Americans safe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
